OL,3,CBoy, 4, was probably septic when seen
OL,4,Cby medical staff, inquest hears
OL,6,FDr Benoy accepted that Daniel was
OL,7,F"probably" septic or "probably at the
OL,8,Fearliest stages," as he gave evidence
OL,9,Fat the inquest into the child's death
OL,10,Fat East London Coroner's Court on
OL,11,FWednesday.
OL,13,FDuring the hearing, at which a number
OL,14,Fof medical staff gave evidence,
OL,15,Fcoroner Mary Hassell said it may
OL,16,Fappear that "a child is admitted at
OL,17,F5pmish septic, and that isn't
OL,18,Frecognised until 9.15pm".
