OL,3,CBoy, 4, was probably septic when seen
OL,4,Cby medical staff, inquest hears
OL,6,FDr Benoy, who said he wanted to get
OL,7,Fassistance from a consultant, said: "I
OL,8,Fthought he was definitely a very
OL,9,Funwell child and needed further
OL,10,Ftreatment. I thought he needed
OL,11,Fadmission and was at risk of sepsis."
OL,13,FHe said Daniel had pulled out a
OL,14,Fcannula, which was being used for
OL,15,Fbloods and fluids, as he was "quite
OL,16,Fdistressed".
OL,18,FDr Benoy said: "Learning from this
OL,19,Fexperience, it surprised me how
OL,20,Fquickly he deteriorated. I did not
OL,21,Fexpect that would happen."
