OL,3,CBoy, 4, was probably septic when seen
OL,4,Cby medical staff, inquest hears
OL,6,FShe saw Daniel some time between 9pm
OL,7,Fand 9.15pm and about 30 minutes after
OL,8,Fhe had been seen by Dr Benoy.
OL,10,FAmong the issues that had been raised
OL,11,Fwas a local infection, a query of
OL,12,Fappendicitis and dehydration, the
OL,13,Fcourt heard.
OL,15,FDr Singh added: "I did not think there
OL,16,Fwas any indication that the child was
OL,17,Fseptic at that time."
OL,19,FThe coroner asked: "Do you think the
OL,20,Freality is that when Dr Benoy saw
OL,21,FDaniel, he was septic?"
OL,26,@wD@QOUyD@UO]{D@TOU}D@WO]
