OL,3,CBoy, 4, was probably septic when seen
OL,4,Cby medical staff, inquest hears
OL,6,FDr Singh replied: "With what we know
OL,7,Fnow in terms of the information, yes
OL,8,Fhe would have been."
OL,10,FThe coroner wondered whether in
OL,11,Fhindsight, and including everything
OL,12,Fthat is now known, including Daniel's
OL,13,Fdeath, if it is possible the child was
OL,14,Fseptic when he arrived for his fourth
OL,15,Fvisit or even his third visit.
OL,17,FOn the possibility of it being the
OL,18,Fthird visit, Dr Singh said: "Sepsis
OL,19,Fcan progress very rapidly. I do not
OL,20,Fknow I'm afraid."
